%description
Performs clustering of quantitative variables, assuming that clusters lie
in low-dimensional subspaces. Segmentation of variables, number of
clusters and their dimensions are selected based on BIC. Candidate models
are identified based on many runs of K-means algorithm with different
random initializations of cluster centers.

